channel.title: How Did You Get Your Internet Name?
channel.description:
Everyone was once that point where they started using a computer and didn't have a name but their own real name to use. How did you get yours? I'll start.
When [i]playing[/i] MoparScape 3.2, I would always sit there spawning a bunch of items. It took a long time, and because of my computer, sometimes if I pressed keys too fast the client wouldn't pick them all up. I would always use Link as my name since I was/am a huge Zelda fan, but one day it skipped the 'k' and didn't realize it until I had spawned the most items I ever had. I decided to stick with it ever since. :)
~Lin

item.title: How Did You Get Your Internet Name?
item.dc:creator: @xryz xryz
item.description:
@xryz wrote:

I made mine up one day in social studies class in 7th grade I believe. I was like I want to make something different from my name. so I messed with the K and make it an X; obviously kept the R because I couldn’t think of anything to change it to; I was change to Y because of the couple of words that make an i sound but spelled with a y e.g. Thyme; finally the S to a Z because they are kind opposite in the direction they start. Plus they all stay connected together when I first wrote them(I would have to take a picture and post to show this).

I got a nickname, Froggy, when I started boy scouts(also in middle school) that they still call me sometimes but I hadn’t every thought of using that for the internet. They gave me that nickname because of froggy from the little rascals; I don’t remember if they said I sounded like him or looked like him.

Also in middle school people called me joe dirt because they said I had a mullet because I’ve always had long hair for the most part.

(From this point on this information isn’t to change the subject; Please to not start a religous discussion because of what I’m about to say. I am simply stating a nickname people have called me and my beliefs/feelings on being called this name. So Please keep this thread on topic thank you.)

They later(in high school) started calling me Jesus because my bangs and all my hair got to be about the same length and they said I looked like Jesus. People in College also called me that. Some people would say that would be an honor to have people think I look like Jesus but I feel like that soils his name because I am know where near as good and sinless as he was.

Read full topic
